  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Cincinnati.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My first position was in Dothan, Alabama, which was a congregation that had been started a few years before, had just almost finished building its synagogue.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was the first rabbi ever to reside in that community, which was quite an experience as a-- as an immigrant, to come to a town where there were about 20 Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The congregation eventually had about 50 families.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the remaining 25 or 30 families were scattered over an area in Alabama, Georgia, and Florida, an area about the size of the state of New Jersey.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the rabbi-- the-- many of them came quite regularly to services, at least on the High Holidays.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- but the rabbi had to travel-- [LAUGHS] --over that area in order to stay in touch with his members so that they would know that they-- they are affiliated.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a very, very interesting way of not only learning the-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] learning the-- the ins and outs of the rabbinate, but also to find out about life in rural America.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because Dothan, a town of about 25,000, 30,000 people, was the center of a farming area, with both cotton and peanuts being the-- the main-- main basis for the-- the industry.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was really the-- the best kind of-- of having to learn, because there was nobody there to-- to help you and to instruct you.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The closest rabbi was 120 miles away in Montgomery.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- in every community, the-- the activities to try to-- to bring refugees over were, if not led, certainly participated in by the-- by the rabbis.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
